cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision, specifically on learning a single visual representation that can be utilized in the analysis of different types of images. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning networks and residual adapter modules, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of parameter sharing, which is a common technique in neural networks and optimization, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper introduces a benchmark for evaluating the ability of representations to capture multiple visual domains, which falls under the scope of cs.MM (Multimedia).
